{
  "texts": [
    "These features are then fed into parallel subnetworks: one subnet calculates mixing weights, while the others, starting with different convolution sizes, extract features across various receptive fields.",
    "The outputs from these subnets are combined to form a cohesive aggregated output, representing the FMB's contribution to enhancing the image's detail and texture.",
    "Loss Function:",
    "where, f (x i, θ) = Reconstructed hyperspectral image, y i = Ground truth hyperspectral image.",
    "The efficacy of the SAPWNet model comes from its incorporation of the dual self-attention mechanisms, which jointly enables the model to comprehensively comprehend both localized and global contextual information within the dataset (Liu and Zhao 2020)."
  ]
}